<lb/><p rend="no-indent">&#8453; <persName>Mr. Crosher</persName> <space extent="1" unit="chars"/> <add rend="black gray" place="inspace" hand="#U">C129/128</add></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="3" unit="words"/><placeName>12 Blue Cross St.</placeName>
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><settlement>Haymarket
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/>S.W.</settlement>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><date when="1881-08-16">August 16/81</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>F.W. Chesson Esq.</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Sir,</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/>I am sorry to intrude
<lb/>on your valuable time again
<lb/>but I will be very brief.
<lb/>I have been employed <w>tempor<seg type="hyphen">-</seg>
<lb/>arily</w> for a few weeks as a
<lb/>messenger &amp; I now am sure
<lb/>I could get a promotion as
<lb/>clerk if I could only get
<lb/>a decent suit of clothes.
<lb/>"a cast off" one from any

	<pb facs="liv_020075_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>of your friends would do.
<lb/>Please do your best for me
<lb/>&amp; I'll be very grateful.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Yrs respectfully
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><persName>W. I. Craft</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend= "no-indent">P.S. An early answer will oblige</p>

			</div>
